```
error[unsafe-isinstance-narrowing]: `MethodNominal` unsafely overlaps with protocol `MethodProto`
  --> src/mdtest_snippet.py:19:5
   |
18 | def check_isinstance(method_nominal: MethodNominal, attribute_nominal: AttributeNominal, obj: object):
19 |     isinstance(method_nominal, MethodProto)  # error: [unsafe-isinstance-narrowing]
   |     ^^^^^^^^^^^--------------^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
   |                |
   |                Has type `MethodNominal`
20 |     isinstance(method_nominal, AttributeProto)  # error: [unsafe-isinstance-narrowing]
21 |     isinstance(attribute_nominal, MethodProto)  # error: [unsafe-isinstance-narrowing]
   |
info: `MethodNominal` has all the members of `MethodProto`, but with incompatible types
info: Runtime `isinstance` checks against protocols only check for the presence of the required members, not their types
info: rule `unsafe-isinstance-narrowing` is enabled by default

```

